WEBVTT

00:04.166 --> 00:07.542
Okay, we have 90 seconds
before Demetrius Pertz

00:07.542 --> 00:09.375
walks into this park
with a briefcase

00:09.375 --> 00:11.709
of weapons-grade uranium.

00:11.709 --> 00:14.125
-Whoa.
-Yes.

00:14.125 --> 00:18.458
Smith, the rendezvous point
is there, by that fountain.

00:18.458 --> 00:21.083
You have the untraceable
South African Krugerrands

00:21.083 --> 00:22.417
to make the exchange?

00:23.208 --> 00:25.291
Where will the support
team be, sir?

00:25.291 --> 00:28.125
We'll be in the last place
he expects --

00:28.125 --> 00:29.333
that bush.

00:30.208 --> 00:32.917
Holding the last thing
he expects --

00:32.917 --> 00:36.166
this net I bought
at True Value hardware.

00:36.166 --> 00:38.208
Now, this could be
our only chance.

00:38.208 --> 00:41.041
Pertz can smell a rat
through a lead wall.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.333
Is that
a real expression?

00:42.333 --> 00:45.083
Great question, Smith!

00:45.083 --> 00:47.208
Bush squad, mount up!

00:51.166 --> 00:53.000
-Hey!
-Sorry, señor.

00:53.000 --> 00:54.208
This is my spot.

00:54.208 --> 00:56.208
Well, not today.
Just go over there.

00:56.208 --> 00:57.834
This is always my spot.

00:57.834 --> 01:00.792
It was my grandfather's spot,
my father's spot.

01:00.792 --> 01:03.208
I hope, one day,
to be my son's spot.

01:03.208 --> 01:05.500
Well, your son's gonna
be selling fruit to mutants

01:05.500 --> 01:07.333
if I don't stop
this uranium dealer.

01:07.333 --> 01:09.000
My son?
No!

01:09.000 --> 01:11.083
Go on,
get out of here!

01:12.000 --> 01:13.959
Go on,
get out of here!

01:13.959 --> 01:16.041
Whoa.
That was weird.

01:16.041 --> 01:18.333
I said,
"Get out of here"!

01:18.333 --> 01:21.000
I said,
"Get out of here"!

01:21.000 --> 01:23.000
What the hell
is happening?

01:23.000 --> 01:25.458
Smith,
I have eyes on Pertz.

01:25.458 --> 01:26.667
Are you in position?

01:26.667 --> 01:28.375
No.
But let me explain why.

01:28.375 --> 01:30.500
Damn it, Smith,
get out of here!

01:31.166 --> 01:32.750
Get out of here!

01:32.750 --> 01:34.667
I know this doesn't
make any sense,

01:34.667 --> 01:36.917
but suddenly I don't
want to be alone.

01:36.917 --> 01:38.291
I can't be alone.

01:38.291 --> 01:42.041
♪

01:42.041 --> 01:43.250
You're blowing it, Smith.

01:43.250 --> 01:45.000
You're blowing
the whole mission.

01:45.000 --> 01:47.333
♪

01:47.333 --> 01:49.625
He has a jet pack!
Get the net!

01:49.625 --> 01:51.166
Get the net!

01:53.166 --> 01:54.917
♪

01:57.041 --> 01:58.792
Smith, you idiot.

01:58.792 --> 02:00.375
You let Pertz get away.

02:00.375 --> 02:04.834
You, however, captured 30
guava, my favorite fruit.

02:04.834 --> 02:08.208
I may have another mission
for you.

02:11.083 --> 02:13.166
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:13.166 --> 02:17.041
♪ I got a feelin' that
it's gonna be a wonderful day ♪

02:17.041 --> 02:20.291
♪ The sun in the sky
has a smile on his face ♪

02:20.291 --> 02:24.750
♪ And he's shinin' a salute
to the American race ♪

02:26.542 --> 02:29.959
♪ Oh, boy, it's swell to say ♪

02:29.959 --> 02:32.500
♪ Good -- ♪
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:32.500 --> 02:33.583
Aah!

02:35.166 --> 02:38.166
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:38.166 --> 02:40.083
♪

02:40.083 --> 02:41.375
Honestly, sir, I don't know

02:41.375 --> 02:42.750
what made me feel
so clingy before,

02:42.750 --> 02:44.041
but I'll be fine.

02:44.041 --> 02:45.375
No, no.
I am fine.

02:45.375 --> 02:46.625
Are you, Smith?

02:46.625 --> 02:48.166
Because you're taking
a shit with me.

02:48.166 --> 02:49.709
Ha! Yes, I am.

02:49.709 --> 02:52.375
You made my net
look like a fool.

02:52.375 --> 02:53.709
Get out of here!

02:54.542 --> 02:56.250
Get out of here!

02:56.250 --> 02:57.625
I don't want to go.

02:57.625 --> 02:59.000
You need to sort this out.

02:59.000 --> 03:01.166
I can't have you blowing
another mission.

03:01.166 --> 03:03.542
Now, hand me
that stack of paper.

03:03.542 --> 03:04.709
What are these?

03:04.709 --> 03:07.041
These are tweets
from my haters.

03:07.041 --> 03:09.458
I use them for toilet paper
to remind myself

03:09.458 --> 03:11.208
they can't get to me.

03:11.208 --> 03:14.500
Take that,
@DominosPizza.

03:14.500 --> 03:17.083
You did this to yourself.

03:17.083 --> 03:19.625
♪

03:24.083 --> 03:28.250
Oh ho!
Epic fail!

03:29.709 --> 03:31.166
Should we be following him?

03:31.166 --> 03:33.583
Are we -- are we sure we want
to make that our thing?

03:33.583 --> 03:35.291
I mean, sometimes it feels
like we only

03:35.291 --> 03:37.166
get to do
one fun thing a week.

03:37.166 --> 03:38.542
True.

03:38.542 --> 03:42.208
Do we really want to put
all of our energy and creativity

03:42.208 --> 03:44.709
into whatever the hell
Klaus has going on?

03:44.709 --> 03:46.667
It will probably be funny.

03:46.667 --> 03:49.333
Oh, Gwen Stefani,
Gwen Stefani.

03:49.333 --> 03:50.417
No Doubt, No Doubt.

03:50.417 --> 03:52.291
See? Like that.

03:52.291 --> 03:57.000
Do we want to pour that kind
of magic into Klaus' shit soup?

03:58.166 --> 03:59.291
"F" it, I'll do it.

03:59.291 --> 04:01.250
-Yeah, me too.
-What the hell.

04:01.250 --> 04:02.667
I'm not gonna commit
quite yet.

04:02.667 --> 04:04.917
I've been planting a lot
of seeds, socially,

04:04.917 --> 04:07.792
and I just know that
as soon as I'm unavailable,

04:07.792 --> 04:09.417
everybody's gonna
want a piece of me.

04:09.417 --> 04:13.125
Social butterfly,
that's who I'll be.

04:13.125 --> 04:15.333
Spreading his wings.

04:17.208 --> 04:19.041
Should probably eat something
while I have time,

04:19.041 --> 04:20.709
before it gets crazy.

04:23.458 --> 04:25.250
♪

04:25.250 --> 04:26.583
I'd like to know
a little more

04:26.583 --> 04:29.166
about these flashbacks
you've been having.

04:29.166 --> 04:30.542
I'm sorry, Dr. Ray.

04:30.542 --> 04:33.208
It's just, dude,
I saw you die.

04:33.208 --> 04:34.583
Right, right.

04:34.583 --> 04:37.542
You say we had both been
miniaturized, was it?

04:37.542 --> 04:40.834
And my head was bitten off
by a giant ant?

04:40.834 --> 04:43.667
The ant wasn't giant,
it was normal size.

04:43.667 --> 04:45.959
We were very small.

04:45.959 --> 04:47.083
What are you writing?

04:47.083 --> 04:50.500
Oh, I just drew a little
picture of a nut.

04:50.500 --> 04:54.166
Your separation anxiety
has severely compromised

04:54.166 --> 04:55.875
your ability
to do your job.

04:55.875 --> 04:59.417
So no more talk about a wild
C.I.A. shrink ray

04:59.417 --> 05:02.000
or some fantastical
clone technology

05:02.000 --> 05:04.208
that could bring
a dead man back to life.

05:04.208 --> 05:07.333
Let's be in the real world,
where I hook you up

05:07.333 --> 05:09.000
to a mental visualizer

05:09.000 --> 05:11.750
that will print a photo
of your thoughts.

05:13.000 --> 05:16.667
It won't... I-I can't...
I don't see him.

05:16.667 --> 05:17.667
Then forget it.

05:17.667 --> 05:19.500
You're wasting my time.

05:19.500 --> 05:21.000
Go away!

05:22.041 --> 05:23.875
Go away!

05:25.667 --> 05:27.000
Here's your man.

05:27.000 --> 05:28.959
Oh, my God!

05:29.917 --> 05:31.500
It's Curly Neal, sir,

05:31.500 --> 05:33.291
the legendary
Harlem Globetrotter.

05:33.291 --> 05:36.291
Somehow, he's responsible
for my separation anxiety.

05:36.291 --> 05:40.375
Listen, Smith, I'm still
upset about Demetrius Pertz.

05:40.375 --> 05:41.959
He made it to U.S. soil,

05:41.959 --> 05:43.750
where the C.I.A.
can't operate

05:43.750 --> 05:46.750
because of craven
judicial overreach.

05:46.750 --> 05:49.667
-You mean laws?
-You mean laws?

05:49.667 --> 05:50.709
Okay, you're in a mood.

05:50.709 --> 05:53.625
I'm gonna go deal
with this.

05:53.625 --> 05:55.959
♪

05:55.959 --> 05:58.083
All right.
Klaus, what's going on?

05:58.083 --> 05:59.667
Yeah, dazzle us, fish.

05:59.667 --> 06:02.250
I have a website.

06:02.250 --> 06:04.041
Klaustastrophe.tv.

06:04.041 --> 06:06.875
It's where I document
all the epic fails around me.

06:06.875 --> 06:07.875
See?

06:13.000 --> 06:14.166
Forgot my keys.

06:16.917 --> 06:18.583
Gesundheit.

06:18.583 --> 06:21.000
-Actually, that was a cough.
-Oh.

06:28.917 --> 06:31.125
Klaus, do you even know
what an epic fail is?

06:31.125 --> 06:34.250
Yeah, Klaus, I was just
crying about my life.

06:34.250 --> 06:35.667
It's not that big a deal.

06:35.667 --> 06:37.834
Steve was right to hold out
for something better.

06:37.834 --> 06:39.000
Why?
What's he got going on?

06:39.000 --> 06:40.667
He's going to
Rhode Island with Stan

06:40.667 --> 06:42.583
to see
the Harlem Globetrotters.

06:42.583 --> 06:44.625
Goddamn Klaus.

06:44.625 --> 06:46.667
♪

06:46.667 --> 06:47.959
Best day ever.

06:47.959 --> 06:50.458
First we got to fly
Southwest Airlines

06:50.458 --> 06:52.500
in boarding group "C"
for cool.

06:52.500 --> 06:54.083
That's what it stands for.

06:54.083 --> 06:57.667
Now we're gonna watch some
former junior college ball hogs

06:57.667 --> 07:00.208
light it up
in the same building

07:00.208 --> 07:03.375
that, just 24 hours
from now, will host

07:03.375 --> 07:05.583
Sesame Street on Ice.

07:05.583 --> 07:07.041
Ladies and gentlemen,

07:07.041 --> 07:09.375
the world-famous
Harlem Globetrotters.

07:09.375 --> 07:12.500
The road to Curly
starts here.

07:12.500 --> 07:13.583
Here they come!

07:13.583 --> 07:15.500
To answer for their sins.

07:15.500 --> 07:17.166
They're amazing, Steve!

07:17.166 --> 07:18.542
At keeping secrets.

07:18.542 --> 07:19.583
I'll kill them
if I have to!

07:19.583 --> 07:20.834
Wrong voice.

07:29.917 --> 07:33.500
Hey, guys, how about joining
us for a magic circle?

07:33.500 --> 07:34.667
Not the first time

07:34.667 --> 07:36.834
I've gotten that invitation
from a gentleman.

07:47.417 --> 07:48.750
Whew.

07:50.542 --> 07:51.875
Your turn, pops.

07:51.875 --> 07:53.667
No, wait,
I don't know how to...

07:59.542 --> 08:06.709
♪

08:09.834 --> 08:11.959
Aah!
Don't get me wet!

08:12.834 --> 08:16.125
It's not water.
It's a miracle!

08:18.917 --> 08:22.250
Go on, Stan, we don't
want you anymore.

08:24.083 --> 08:25.458
That's it.

08:25.458 --> 08:29.583
When I was 9 years old,
I went to Globetrotters camp.

08:29.583 --> 08:31.375
I had the best month of my life.

08:31.375 --> 08:34.375
And then, for no reason,
they kicked me out.

08:34.375 --> 08:36.041
Wow, that's rough.

08:36.041 --> 08:38.083
But are you too upset
to take a half-court shot

08:38.083 --> 08:41.542
for a lifetime supply
of Little Debbie products?

08:41.542 --> 08:42.667
Give me the rock.

08:49.000 --> 08:50.000
Swish.

08:50.000 --> 08:51.917
♪ All I do is win, win, win ♪

08:51.917 --> 08:53.375
♪ No matter what ♪

08:53.375 --> 08:56.125
♪ Got money on my mind,
I can never get enough ♪

08:59.166 --> 09:00.834
♪

09:00.834 --> 09:01.959
I need some answers.

09:01.959 --> 09:03.291
You missed the shot.
You don't get the food.

09:03.291 --> 09:05.375
No. Why did Curly
and the Globetrotters

09:05.375 --> 09:06.375
kick me out of camp?

09:06.375 --> 09:07.625
How long ago was this?

09:07.625 --> 09:08.709
34 years.

09:08.709 --> 09:10.000
I'm 24.

09:10.000 --> 09:11.917
I would have been
minus 10 years old.

09:11.917 --> 09:12.959
That's a small number.

09:12.959 --> 09:15.208
That's a small integer.

09:15.208 --> 09:18.709
Junior college
is still college.

09:18.709 --> 09:20.709
All right.
Time to hit the showers.

09:20.709 --> 09:22.834
And don't just sprinkle
water on your hair.

09:22.834 --> 09:24.250
I'll be able to tell.

09:24.250 --> 09:26.709
These kids don't know
where to find Curly,

09:26.709 --> 09:28.500
but I do.

09:28.500 --> 09:38.000
♪

09:38.000 --> 09:40.333
It's just
a little further.

09:40.333 --> 09:42.458
Couldn't you have just
written these directions down?

09:42.458 --> 09:45.041
Ooh!
Am I such bad company?

09:45.041 --> 09:46.875
Well, good luck
finding him yourself.

09:50.250 --> 09:51.792
Damn it!

09:53.083 --> 09:56.083
Have your epic fails
not been epic enough?

09:56.083 --> 10:00.875
Try giving your smoothie
a kick with an M-80 berry.

10:07.875 --> 10:09.709
If it can clean a golf club,

10:09.709 --> 10:12.625
imagine what it
can do for teeth.

10:12.625 --> 10:15.000
♪

10:25.375 --> 10:29.333
Roger is about to learn,
when you snooze, you lose.

10:36.709 --> 10:38.041
Aah!

10:39.792 --> 10:43.333
♪

10:48.667 --> 10:51.959
-Wait. Is that...
-It can't be...

10:51.959 --> 10:54.333
-Is it?
-Stan Smith.

10:54.333 --> 10:55.375
Curly?

10:55.375 --> 10:58.458
I thought I'd never
see you again.

10:58.458 --> 11:01.750
Curly, I traveled
a long way to see you.

11:01.750 --> 11:03.041
Traveling
is a violation.

11:03.041 --> 11:05.291
Curly's ball
on the porch.

11:05.291 --> 11:07.875
So they got you all
the way out here, huh?

11:07.875 --> 11:09.417
Yeah, we stay isolated

11:09.417 --> 11:11.166
in case another
Space Jam happens

11:11.166 --> 11:13.458
and they need us
to defeat the Monstars.

11:13.458 --> 11:15.041
So I hear you remember

11:15.041 --> 11:16.917
those dribbling tricks
I taught you.

11:16.917 --> 11:19.375
Well, my dazzle catch
was slow to -- Hold on.

11:19.375 --> 11:21.083
We can't just sit here
like friends.

11:21.083 --> 11:23.333
You guys abandoned me.
You kicked me out of your camp.

11:23.333 --> 11:25.875
Oh, Stan,
there's no such thing

11:25.875 --> 11:28.208
as Globetrotter camp.
-What?!

11:28.208 --> 11:30.917
We had just played a show.

11:30.917 --> 11:32.834
And as we were leaving,

11:32.834 --> 11:34.709
we saw you waiting
for your dad.

11:34.709 --> 11:38.625
An usher told us he had pounded
a Sprite, burped the words

11:38.625 --> 11:42.458
"Time for some strange,"
and jogged off into the night.

11:42.458 --> 11:43.792
We offered to take you home,

11:43.792 --> 11:45.625
but you didn't know
where you lived.

11:45.625 --> 11:48.667
My dad said it was important
I never know our address

11:48.667 --> 11:49.875
in case I was ever captured

11:49.875 --> 11:51.417
and tortured by people
looking for him.

11:51.417 --> 11:54.125
Well, that didn't sound
like a great scene to us,

11:54.125 --> 11:57.417
so we took you on the road
and told you it was camp.

11:57.417 --> 12:00.625
And you trotted
around the globe with us

12:00.625 --> 12:03.083
on a bus up
and down I-70.

12:03.083 --> 12:05.792
But 4 weeks later,
your dad showed up,

12:05.792 --> 12:07.125
and we had
to give you back.

12:07.125 --> 12:09.041
Except you didn't
like that idea.

12:09.041 --> 12:11.208
No, I'm staying
with you guys.

12:11.208 --> 12:15.125
Well, you can't, because...

12:17.709 --> 12:21.709
We don't want you
around, okay?!

12:21.709 --> 12:23.750
Go on,
get out of here!

12:23.750 --> 12:25.959
I said,
"Get out of here"!

12:25.959 --> 12:30.750
♪

12:39.709 --> 12:43.041
So you just said
that stuff

12:43.041 --> 12:44.500
to make me go back
to my dad.

12:44.500 --> 12:47.291
It was the hardest thing
I've ever done.

12:47.291 --> 12:49.166
We all missed you
so much.

12:49.166 --> 12:51.542
We even tried to adopt you,
but 12 black men

12:51.542 --> 12:53.750
asking for custody
of a young white boy

12:53.750 --> 12:55.625
wasn't a slam dunk
back then.

12:55.625 --> 12:57.375
Or even now, probably.

12:57.375 --> 13:00.000
You don't know how helpful
you've been to me, Curly.

13:00.000 --> 13:01.959
Come back anytime, Stan.

13:01.959 --> 13:03.500
That won't be necessary.

13:05.667 --> 13:07.291
♪

13:07.291 --> 13:09.875
Guess I can say goodbye
to my separation anxiety

13:09.875 --> 13:12.000
because the Globetrotters
didn't abandon me.

13:12.000 --> 13:14.250
My dad did,
which is way worse

13:14.250 --> 13:15.625
'cause that ain't
never going away.

13:22.458 --> 13:25.041
Oh, God,
not that guy again.

13:25.041 --> 13:27.583
♪

13:28.625 --> 13:30.041
You almost killed us.

13:30.041 --> 13:31.834
I was taking your notes.

13:31.834 --> 13:34.166
The fails
are so epic now.

13:34.166 --> 13:36.375
Traffic is up,
so is ad revenue.

13:36.375 --> 13:38.458
People are actually
watching this?

13:38.458 --> 13:39.458
Hundreds!

13:39.458 --> 13:41.709
And you can make money
from it?

13:41.709 --> 13:43.000
Thousands.

13:43.000 --> 13:44.750
It will take more than just
shouting numbers

13:44.750 --> 13:46.041
to get me on board.

13:46.041 --> 13:47.417
Millions!

13:47.417 --> 13:49.583
Well, you called
my bluff, I'm in.

13:49.583 --> 13:54.583
♪

13:54.583 --> 13:55.709
Hi.

13:55.709 --> 13:57.250
I've realized that,
due to my crippling,

13:57.250 --> 13:59.458
father-induced
separation anxiety,

13:59.458 --> 14:02.250
I can no longer be
a reliable member of the team.

14:02.250 --> 14:05.208
Is there a process for becoming
a lone-wolf agent?

14:05.208 --> 14:08.041
I'd like to stop Demetrius Pertz
all by myself,

14:08.041 --> 14:09.417
without my daddy
or anyone.

14:09.417 --> 14:12.291
You'll have to sign
these lone-wolf forms.

14:14.709 --> 14:17.750
Doing what you're told?
You're no lone wolf.

14:17.750 --> 14:20.542
Lone wolves are rebels,
playing by their own rules.

14:20.542 --> 14:22.542
Look at the name
I signed.

14:22.542 --> 14:25.083
Butts McButts.

14:25.083 --> 14:26.875
♪ All I do is win, win, win ♪

14:26.875 --> 14:28.333
♪ No matter what ♪

14:28.333 --> 14:30.959
♪ Got money on my mind,
I can never get enough ♪

14:33.667 --> 14:40.667
♪

14:40.667 --> 14:46.250
Demetrius Pertz.
And this time, I'm ready.

14:46.250 --> 14:50.000
The only person I can
get killed is myself.

14:53.750 --> 14:55.542
Well,
you're halfway there.

14:55.542 --> 14:57.959
♪

14:57.959 --> 14:59.417
See, Klaus?
This is what you get

14:59.417 --> 15:01.625
when you work with us
on the epic fails.

15:01.625 --> 15:04.375
They're just as epic,
but none of us are bleeding

15:04.375 --> 15:07.000
on either the outside
or the inside.

15:08.000 --> 15:11.417
Time to go downstairs
to do the laundry.

15:11.417 --> 15:14.000
Can't think of anything safer.

15:14.000 --> 15:15.417
Whoa!

15:21.250 --> 15:25.250
I'ma dunk
this basketball, for reals.

15:32.208 --> 15:34.041
Movie time!

15:34.041 --> 15:36.291
I hope it's not a scary one.

15:43.000 --> 15:44.917
Ugh! I got a burnt one.

15:46.041 --> 15:49.917
It's so bad, I don't even want
to listen to my catchphrase.

15:49.917 --> 15:51.083
What was bad about it?

15:51.083 --> 15:52.458
Everything.

15:52.458 --> 15:55.500
All those clumsy camera cuts
to hide how fake it was.

15:55.500 --> 15:57.959
Klaustastrophe.tv is over.

15:57.959 --> 16:00.333
Thanks a lot, idiots.

16:02.542 --> 16:05.041
I don't understand.
I did eat that spider.

16:05.041 --> 16:06.583
Why did we cut away from that?

16:06.583 --> 16:10.667
Actually tasted okay, like a
hairy croissant full of blood.

16:13.125 --> 16:15.500
I apologize for
the scratchy ropes.

16:15.500 --> 16:17.291
I bought them
on scratchyropes.com.

16:17.291 --> 16:18.542
I thought it was a joke.

16:18.542 --> 16:20.125
I was like, "No one is
gonna pay full price

16:20.125 --> 16:21.875
for scratchy ropes,"
but here we are.

16:21.875 --> 16:25.417
They got my money,
and you got scratchy ropes.

16:25.417 --> 16:28.417
Anyway, I got a sidewinder
missile sale to finish.

16:28.417 --> 16:30.959
So you're going to
abandon me, too?

16:30.959 --> 16:32.375
Don't worry.

16:32.375 --> 16:35.000
I'll be back in a minute
to kill you.
Whatever.

16:35.000 --> 16:38.333
Go do your thing
that's so important.

16:38.333 --> 16:39.542
This is the worst.

16:39.542 --> 16:41.125
If this rope was any scratchier,

16:41.125 --> 16:43.709
it would be overseen by
the state lottery commission.

16:43.709 --> 16:45.125
Ha ha!

16:45.125 --> 16:47.333
If I had a team with me, someone
would have laughed at that.

16:47.333 --> 16:49.333
You do have a team
with you, Stan.

16:49.333 --> 16:50.834
That just wasn't
very funny.

16:50.834 --> 16:52.250
Curly!

16:54.959 --> 16:56.375
How did you guys find me?

16:56.375 --> 16:58.000
With a little help
from the tracking chip

16:58.000 --> 16:59.208
I implanted in your neck

16:59.208 --> 17:01.041
while I was putting
the visualizer on you.

17:01.041 --> 17:02.875
We may not have caused
your problems,

17:02.875 --> 17:04.792
Stan,
but we can help fix it.

17:04.792 --> 17:07.583
Then come with me,
old men and Dr. Ray.

17:07.583 --> 17:10.000
We've got an arms deal
to stop.

17:10.000 --> 17:14.583
♪

17:14.583 --> 17:16.166
Any chance
any of you are armed?

17:16.166 --> 17:19.792
Just with athletic ability
and a passion for entertainment.

17:19.792 --> 17:21.458
Right!
Right.

17:22.542 --> 17:23.709
Grenade!

17:23.709 --> 17:25.709
Magic circle!

17:25.709 --> 17:28.375
♪

17:31.083 --> 17:32.208
Wait, guys,
get rid of it.

17:32.208 --> 17:36.333
♪

17:40.083 --> 17:42.375
Okay, that's nice.

17:43.291 --> 17:44.917
Goose,
you still got it, man.

17:44.917 --> 17:46.083
Okay, big finish now.

17:46.083 --> 17:47.041
Now, now, now, now, now!

17:47.041 --> 17:50.417
♪

17:53.417 --> 17:55.458
Again! Do it again!

17:56.375 --> 17:58.250
Okay, so we make a circle.

18:00.333 --> 18:02.667
-No!
-Boo!

18:02.667 --> 18:06.667
Sorry, Stan, turns out we're not
much of a rescue party.

18:07.834 --> 18:11.166
How about
one last magic circle?

18:13.375 --> 18:14.834
Goodbye, guys.

18:14.834 --> 18:16.750
Thanks for being there
for me.

18:19.208 --> 18:21.959
Is anybody hit?
-No.

18:21.959 --> 18:23.709
The circle really
is magic!

18:23.709 --> 18:26.417
Yes, it magically
took credit for me

18:26.417 --> 18:28.208
shooting
all these bad guys.

18:29.375 --> 18:31.208
Sir!
How did you find me?

18:31.208 --> 18:32.417
I had you chipped.

18:32.417 --> 18:34.458
You're remarkably easy
to chip.

18:34.458 --> 18:36.625
There are,
like, seven in you.

18:36.625 --> 18:38.583
But why?
I quit the team.

18:38.583 --> 18:40.166
Don't be a dumbass, Stan.

18:40.166 --> 18:41.625
You'll always be
part of the team.

18:41.625 --> 18:43.417
Then you'll die together!

18:45.250 --> 18:46.333
Thanks, Coach!

18:46.333 --> 18:49.166
Don't thank me,
thank rolling.

18:49.166 --> 18:51.583
♪

18:51.583 --> 18:55.458
Look, guys, I'm -- I'm sorry
I yelled at you before.

18:55.458 --> 18:57.834
I mean, the website
isn't that important.

18:57.834 --> 18:59.875
So, I scraped together
a few bucks

18:59.875 --> 19:04.250
for a little apology party
if you're interested.

19:06.208 --> 19:08.709
Grab a seat.
Dig in.

19:11.125 --> 19:14.166
Epic fail!

19:14.166 --> 19:15.500
What the hell, Klaus?

19:15.500 --> 19:17.875
Your junk was so lame.

19:17.875 --> 19:20.792
This is the primo stuff
that goes right into

19:20.792 --> 19:21.875
the public's veins.

19:21.875 --> 19:24.333
Yes!
Whoa!

19:24.333 --> 19:26.417
Nein!
Aah!

19:26.417 --> 19:28.542
Oh, no.
My cup.

19:28.542 --> 19:30.750
I need water,
or I'll die.

19:30.750 --> 19:32.333
What are we supposed to do?

19:32.333 --> 19:34.375
Spit on me.

19:37.500 --> 19:39.083
It's not enough.

19:39.083 --> 19:40.875
I need more liquid.

19:40.875 --> 19:43.375
You'll have to...

19:43.375 --> 19:45.500
Whoa. That's where
your pee comes out?

19:45.500 --> 19:47.875
-Sometimes.
-Wait, is the camera still on?

19:47.875 --> 19:50.041
Turn it off!
Don't film this!

19:50.041 --> 19:51.709
My turn.

19:51.709 --> 19:54.041
♪

19:54.041 --> 19:55.792
So I guess what I'm saying is,

19:55.792 --> 19:57.542
even though I discovered
yet another way

19:57.542 --> 19:59.208
my dad really screwed me up,

19:59.208 --> 20:02.333
I realized I don't have to worry
about being abandoned.

20:02.333 --> 20:05.417
There are people in my life
who love and care about me

20:05.417 --> 20:07.792
and will always be there
for me --

20:07.792 --> 20:11.000
the Harlem Globetrotters
and my friends from work.

20:11.875 --> 20:15.417
The pattern of abandonment
has been broken.

20:15.417 --> 20:17.458
Where is Steve?

20:19.417 --> 20:21.792
Look, Steve,
there's no such thing

20:21.792 --> 20:24.041
as Sesame Street on Ice camp.

20:24.041 --> 20:26.583
Your dad just abandoned
you at the arena.

20:26.583 --> 20:30.166
No, I want to stay
with you guys.

20:30.166 --> 20:32.417
Well, you can't.

20:32.417 --> 20:35.834
Because...

20:35.834 --> 20:37.667
we don't
want you around, okay?!

20:37.667 --> 20:39.917
Go on,
get out of here!

20:39.917 --> 20:42.041
I said,
"Get out of here"!

20:43.208 --> 20:50.875
♪

20:52.709 --> 20:55.875
It's okay, Marcus.
It's okay.

20:55.875 --> 20:57.750
We've got four other kids
in the van

20:57.750 --> 20:59.834
that nobody is coming for.

21:01.125 --> 21:03.041
Bye-bye!
See you soon!

21:05.166 --> 21:06.000
-- Captions by VITAC --
